OL,3,CUK inflation rises to 3.8%, driven by
OL,4,Chigh accommodation and travel costs
OL,6,FUK inflation rose by more than
OL,7,Fexpected in July as demand for summer
OL,8,Ftravel pushed up air fares and food
OL,9,Fprices continued to climb, according
OL,10,Fto official figures.
OL,12,FThe Office for National Statistics
OL,13,F(ONS) published the latest inflation
OL,14,Fdata on Wednesday, showing the rate of
OL,15,FConsumer Prices Index (CPI) rose from
OL,16,FJune's figure of 3.6% to 3.8%.
OL,18,FMost economists had been forecasting
OL,19,Finflation to rise to 3.7%.
