OL,3,CUK inflation rises to 3.8%, driven by
OL,4,Chigh accommodation and travel costs
OL,6,FIt means the headline rate remained at
OL,7,Fthe highest level since January 2024,
OL,8,Fwhen it hit 4%, with Chancellor Rachel
OL,9,FReeves warning there was "more to do
OL,10,Fto ease the cost of living".
OL,12,FThe ONS said the school summer
OL,13,Fholidays helped bump up travel costs
OL,14,Fin July, which helped drive up
OL,15,Finflation across the UK.
OL,17,FONS Chief Economist Grant Fitzner
OL,18,Fsaid: "Inflation rose again this month
OL,19,Fto its highest annual rate since the
OL,20,Fbeginning of last year.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
