OL,4,Chigh accommodation and travel costs
OL,6,FMeanwhile, food and drink inflation
OL,7,Frose to 4.9% in July, from 4.5% in
OL,8,FJune.
OL,10,FThis marked the fourth month in a row
OL,11,Fthat the annual rate had increased and
OL,12,Fremained at the highest level since
OL,13,FFebruary 2024.
OL,15,FVictoria Scholar, head of investment
OL,16,Ffor Interactive Investor, said there
OL,17,Fwere "particular worries about
OL,18,Fdomestic food price inflation as well
OL,19,Fas uncertainty around how Trump's
OL,20,Ftariffs could push up prices."
